283
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:53,030
The hardest part is that card.
The card is a killer.

284
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:55,156
I never know what it's
supposed to say.

285
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:58,630
And it's getting so tough, because
the relationships are so complicated...

286
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:02,475
...greeting-card companies now
put out cards that are blank...

287
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:04,232
...on the inside. Nothing.

288
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:06,630
No message.
It's like the card company says:

289
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:08,631
"We give up.
You think of something."

290
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:12,634
You know? " For 7 5 cents,
I don't want to get involved."

291
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,875
- Maybe you won't like it.
- How could I not like it?

292
00:15:17,040 --> 00:15:19,429
- Of course I'll like it.
- You could not like it.

293
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:22,478
Just the fact that you remembered
means everything.

294
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:23,914
Of course I remembered.

295
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:26,674
You reminded me every day
for two months.

296
00:15:27,480 --> 00:15:29,118
Oh, the card.

297
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:46,390
- Cash?
- What do you think?

298
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:49,794
You got me cash?

299
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:53,351
This way, I figure you could go out
and get yourself whatever you want.

300
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:54,919
No good?

301
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:56,513
Who are you, my uncle?

302
00:15:56,680 --> 00:16:00,116
Hey. Come on, it's $1 82 there. I don't
think that's anything to sneeze at.

303
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:06,631
Let me see the card.

304
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:16,915
"To a wonderful girl, a great pal...

305
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:19,150
...and more."

306
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:22,988
Hey.

307
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:27,758
Elaine, I'm glad you're here. Stay right
here. I'm gonna be right back. Stay.

308
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:31,993
" Pal"? You think I'm your pal?

309
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:34,151
I said, "and more."

310
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:39,632
I am not your pal.

311
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:43,031
What's wrong with pal?
Why is everybody so down on pal?

312
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:46,749
- Hey.
- Oh, what is this?

313
00:16:46,920 --> 00:16:49,593
- You got me something?
- Yeah. Yeah, open it.

314
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:52,231
Kramer!

315
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:56,272
The bench! You got me
the bench that I wanted!

316
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:03,352
- That's pretty good, huh?
- Great.

317
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:06,239
You remember when she mentioned it?
I made a mental note of it.

318
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:08,312
Well, goody for you.

319
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:10,835
Yeah. See, I'm very sensitive
about that.

320
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:14,913
I mean, someone's birthday comes up,
I keep my ears open.

321
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:16,713
So, what did you get her?

322
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:20,073
1 82 bucks.

323
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:23,037
Cash?

324
00:17:23,520 --> 00:17:26,114
You've gotta be kidding.
What kind of gift is that?

325
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:29,078
That's like something
her uncle would give her.

326
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:34,793
"Think where man's glory
most begins and ends...

327
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:39,033
...and say my glory
was I had such a friend."

328
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,991
Yeats.

329
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:45,076
Oh, Kramer.

330
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:51,839
Could you excuse us, please?

331
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,228
